Philippine Banks Ask High Court to Stop Imposing 20% Bond Tax

-- B y   C l a r i s s a   B a t i n o
-- 
2011-10-17T03:46:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-17/philippine-banks-ask-high-court-to-stop-imposing-20-bond-tax.html
Banco de Oro Unibank Inc. (BDO) ,
 Metropolitan Bank & Trust (MBT)  Co. and six other banks today asked
the Philippine Supreme Court to stop the government from
imposing and collecting a 20 percent final withholding tax on
35-billion pesos worth of bonds due tomorrow.  In their petition, local lenders including Bank of
Commerce,  China Banking Corp. (CHIB) ,  Philippine Bank of
Communications (PBC) ,  Philippine National Bank (PNB) , Philippine Veterans
Bank and Planters Development Bank, asked the high court for a
temporary restraining order and a subsequent injunction against
respondents including the Bureau of Internal Revenue and the
Bureau of the Treasury. The government expects to collect almost
5 billion in taxes from the bonds due tomorrow.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Clarissa Batino at 
 cbatino@bloomberg.net  